OL,4,Cnegative phone experiences ` study
OL,6,F"It may not be a surprise, therefore,
OL,7,Fthat they report higher degrees of
OL,8,Fchallenge associated with their
OL,9,Fsmartphone and social media use. In
OL,10,Fthis context, we see this cohort as
OL,11,Fbeing particularly vulnerable to the
OL,12,Fmost troubling dimensions of
OL,13,Fsmartphone use," he added.
OL,15,FResearchers also found a disconnect
OL,16,Fbetween the concerns parents had over
OL,17,Ftheir children's phone use, and the
OL,18,Fnegative experiences students actually
OL,19,Freported.
